data.content:
noun
entre or entree , pl -tres or -trees
[count] :the main dish of a meal especially in a restaurant
We had steak as an entre.
formal
[count] :the act or manner of entering something
She made a graceful entre [=entrance] into the ballroom.
His entre [=entry] into the restaurant business was unexpected.
[noncount] :the right to enter something
His family connections have given him entre [=entry] into the most exclusive clubs in the city.
